-align:left} </style> </head> <body class=\"c6\"> <p class=\"c2\"><span class=\"c3 c5\">Device Management</span> <p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\"></span> </p> <p class=\"c2\"><span class=\"c1\">A. Make sure Bluetooth is 'ON' in the iOS Settings.</span> </p> <p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\"></span> </p> <p class=\"c2\"><span class=\"c1\">B. Never 'pair' the NMX with iOS Settings, only use the NMX Motion app to connect.</span> </p> <p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\"></span> </p> <p class=\"c2\"><span class=\"c1\">C. The Bluetooth indicator light should be OFF when you connect, the light will turn ON when you are connected.</span> </p> <p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\"></span> </p> <p class=\"c2\"><span class=\"c1\">D. Double check that the NMX is displaying 5 blinking lights during power-up.</span> </p> <p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\"></span> </p> <p class=\"c2\"><span class=\"c1\">E. Double check that nothing is interfering or depressing the blue 'Emergency Stop' button.</span> </p> </body>";
    
